I have a use case where `react-optimize` preset breaks the app when build with `--release`, but everything works correctly when run in development mode with `yarn start` since `react-optimize` is not being applied.

Here's na example use case:

`routes/hello/index.js`

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import Layout from '../../components/Layout';
import Hello from './Hello';

export default {

  path: '/hello/:name',

  async action(context, { name }) {
    const upperCasedName = name.trim().toUpperCase();
 
    // awaits should be here but they don't matter in this case

    return {
      component: <Layout><Hello name={upperCasedName} /></Layout>,
    };
  },
};
```

is being optimized to this form

```javascript
/* harmony default export */ __webpack_exports__["default"] = {

  path: '/hello/:name',

  action(context, { name }) {
    var _ref = _jsx(__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__components_Layout__["a" /* default */], {}, void 0, _jsx(__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_2__Hello__["a" /* default */], {
      name: upperCasedName
    }));

    return _asyncToGenerator(function* () {
      const upperCasedName = name.trim().toUpperCase();

      return {
        component: _ref
      };
    })();
  }

};
```

Issue lies here

```javascript
var _ref = _jsx(__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__components_Layout__["a" /* default */], {}, void 0, _jsx(__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_2__Hello__["a" /* default */], {
      name: upperCasedName
    }));
```

`upperCasedName` is not yet defined and app breaks.

